-- Czech Stocks: CEZ, New World Resources, Kit Digital Are Active
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-07-20T15:51:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-20/czech-stocks-cez-new-world-resources-kit-digital-are-active.html
The Czech Republic’s  PX (PX)  stock index
fell 1.3 percent to 898 at the end of trading in Prague. The
gauge ended the week down 0.7 percent.  The following were among the most active  stocks  in the
Czech market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  CEZ AS (CEZ)  , the largest Czech power producer, dropped
1.9 percent, the most this month, to 706 koruna.  New World
Resources NV (NWR)  , the largest producer of coking coal,
slumped 5.2 percent, the most since May 30, to 96.54 koruna.  Stocks and oil dropped as concern that  Europe ’s debt crisis
is slowing global growth drove investors from riskier assets.
Europe’s benchmark coal derivatives snapped a five-day rally,
falling 0.7 percent to $98.10 a metric ton in the Netherlands.  Kit Digital Inc. (KITD)   retreated 7.2 percent to 74.49
koruna, extending its weekly loss to 14 percent, the most since
the five days ended May 18. The software maker said yesterday it
will delist from the Czech bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net . 